<br>
There are some mobs that we want (1) warrior to maintain agro and take ALL melee damage from the mob. INNO, VELK and VINDI for example.<br>
<br>
What we do is before the fight pick the Main tank, then second tank, then third tank etc.<br>
<br>
Then we pick a cleric healing order rotation.<br>
Example:<br>
Daaz then Thuinn then Ael then Maxum then Phix then back to Daaz etc<br>
<br>
So when fight starts the Main tank rushes forward and gets agro asap. All other melee at max range. Daaz would start a CH fairly quickly.....he at the same time shouts in zone "CH inc in 10 seconds on (MT name)....Thuinn you are next" at this time Thuinn makes sure to have the main tank on target....counts to 10 then starts a CH and shouts "Ch inc in 10 seconds on (MT name )....Ael you are next.<br>
Then Ael counts to 10 then starts a CH and shouts "CH inc in 10 seconds on (MT name)....Maxum you are next..<br>
<br>
we do this till last cleric, then Daaz would start over.<br>
<br>
(Depending on how tough the mob hits we will either lengthen or shorten the time between CH's.)<br>
<br>
End result is a CH is landing regularly on the Main Tank and he/she stays alive.<br>
<br>
Problems occur when ch does not land in time and the first main tank dies. The clerics then have to shift to Main Tank 2. This can be tricky because the Mob may decide he hates someone else more than the Main tank 2......this results in a person that is not taking damage to get heals, and someone that is taking damage dies without a heal.<br>
<br>
This is where things go wrong most of the time.<br>
<br>
Solution is.....max range.  Main tank 1 goes in closest....after main tank 1 has been in for a bit and has good agro....main tank 2 steps on and builds agro without taking full agro.<br>
<br>
So if main tank 1 dies, mob switches to main tank 2...and so do clerics.<br>
If others are too close and get agro away from Main Tank 2 on switch everyone else needs to back off, or turn attack off or something to try and help Main tank 2 get agro.<br>
<br>
There are also issues with clerics getting heal agro, but that is usually controlable since heal agro is spread out amongst 4 or 5 clerics.<br>
<br>
This is something we really really really need to practice so we are all on same page.<br>
<br>
If we want to move to next level mobs, we will be using this style a lot. <p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
