<BR>
Life is a succession of lessons which must be lived to be understood.<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ujaraan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jaraan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Recruitment Officer</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/12/02 5:00:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Main tank with CH order.</span><hr size=1> Yeah got to agree with what Sirt and Muff has said. Want to add, that 2nd tank should have a back up healer or the cleric that's last on the rotation in his group, so that when switching from MT to 2nd tank (it can get rough) there's a cleric or backup healer ready to hit with chlorophyll or divine light before CHeals rotation begins on the 2nd tank. <br>
<br>
Also 2nd tank start taunting the mob somewhere after 2-3 Cheals gone off the Main Tank. That way you're building aggro as the fight progresses, but do not over aggro to the point that mob switches target from MT to 2nd tank. Turn attack off once in a while.  <p><center><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=62453>Jaraan Stonebow</a><br><center><b>
Warder of Odysseys</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usinormxev.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SinormXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/14/02 9:16:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Main tank with CH order.</span><hr size=1> How taunt works (pretty sure on this), it causes you to be put on the very top of the hate list, if it works.  You can tell when it works or not on mobs like the clerics in hate, ect, mobs that have a mesage when you taunt.  So, you do not want the 2nd tank taunting, but have him in, building agro for an easy switch.  Also, like Jaraan said, you will need druids, and a few specified clerics to cast sup heal/DL, whatever fast cast heal spell on the new tank at first, becuase these mobs can kill a tank in less than 5 seconds, when a CH takes 10 seconds.  Generally, you will be shooting for a CH to land once every 3 seconds, but this will vary by mob.  On dojo today, we were landing a CH about every 5 seconds or so, and that was plenty.  BTW, Dojo is very good practice for this.  He is an easier mob, but hits hard and requires MT stratagy.  From him we can move on to Velketor, Innoruuk and others.  One vital thing you will notice for this, you want at least 6 clerics for the higher end Velius mobs. <p>Sinorm 57th Myrmidon of Xev</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ugrondarsk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grondarsk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Harm Touched Haflin anyone?</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/16/02 1:10:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fodysseyxevfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Main tank with CH order.</span><hr size=1> Various musing on Hate...<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The Taunt Button: Taunt does not put you at the top of the hate list, necessarily - it is a button that says &quot;give me more hate.&quot; The hate that you get from your taunt button depends on how high your skill in taunt is. Lots of things can get you hate (heals, procs, debuffs, spells, SITTING, proximity, high damage and fast weapons) and each has a certain numerical quantity of hate that accrues.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Frinstance, Grubbnubbnubb gets one billlllllion points of hate for slowing a small mushroom. I start hitting the small mushroom, and hitting the taunt button. The mushroom starts telling me &quot;I'll teach you to interfere with me, Grondar,&quot; indicating that my taunt is working. However, it keeps whacking on Grubby, because my taunt has not reached one billion. This is just how I like it, it keeps him on his toes. I continue to whack on it and taunt, and it keeps indicating its desire to give me detailed instructions on how to interefere with it, until my taunt reaches one billion, or until I decide to let Grubby off the hook and use a spell to taunt. Then it turns on me, full of fungal rage.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp In a deathtouch situation, whoever is at the top of the hate list when the deathtouch resets is the one who eats the deathtouch. A Spiroc Lord says &quot;HOLYSHARK!&quot; Haha, happy bout that Willsapper now? <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp In a MT situation, using defensive disc, what can help to transition tanks is for the second tank to move up from max range and start taunting once the first tank says that def disc is going to wear off. That way, proximity and taunt will make this tank second on the hate list. Or if the second tank is a SK, the SK can just cast a couple of spells that will fill the mob with mindless rage, presto, instant agro.<br>
 =-)<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp One other thing that can cause hate (and is especially nasty with summoning mobs) is low hps. For instance, lets say Derakor the Vindicator is attacking Warrior01 and not getting anywhere since Warrior01 is getting a CH every 5 seconds. At max range (of course) and in a circle so as not to push the mob all around the arena (of course) some of the other tanks are going to get punished by Mr. Derakor's riposte. This is ok for a while, but Derakor is a sucker for an easy mark, and when Ranger01 or SK02 gets to around a bubble of health, they will be summarily summoned and killed, because their low health will be an irresistable taunt. This is not just super high level mobs -- in Oasis, for example, try taunting an orc warrior off of a fleeing mage with less than a bubble of health. The orc warrior may turn on you and attack you next, but probably after killing the mage. What is the cure for this problem in a CH rotation? Our wonderful back up healers who are not part of the CH rotation.<br>
<br>
Grondar Gutguzzler<br>
